{
  "texts": [
    "GraphAide represents a significant advancement in the development of domain-specific digital assistants, integrating state-of-the-art GenAI and semantic technologies for improved performance and extensibility.",
    "GraphAide is an agentic retrieval-augmented generation (RAG)-based system that employs multiple LLM instances to perform diverse tasks.",
    "Agent-based LLM applications utilize the reasoning capabilities of an LLM to determine the appropriate sequence of actions in response to user queries.",
    "Unlike hardcoded instructions (i.e., chains), an agentic application can comprehend the LLM's response and construct subsequent queries dynamically.",
    "GraphAide is a hybrid application leveraging both chains and agents to handle a variety of user queries."
  ]
}